<br>
Does it not concern you that members of Congress are barred from attending these meetings?  Or that the development of 'bunker-busting' nukes (from a certain point of view <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) can simply be seen as part and parcel of the current administration's concept of US pre-emptive attack, military &amp; economic dominance, and the other euphemisms for empire building that the Pentagon hawks like to bandy about.<br>
<br>
